## Overview

The FTP/SFTP File Server connection type links a vault to a remote file server, enabling automated file upload, download, and monitoring. It supports both FTP and SFTP protocols for transferring files to and from your organization's file infrastructure. Use this when your organization stores data files — such as exports, reports, or intake files — on an FTP or SFTP server and you want Graphium to automatically read from or write to that server. To configure this connection, you must have an Admin or Builder vault role with access to the vault's Connections section, valid server credentials (hostname, username, and password or SSH key), and network access to the file server from Graphium.

## Step-by-Step Instructions

### Step 1: Open the Add Connection Picker

In the vault sidebar, click **Connections**, then click **+ Add Connection**.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/connections/connections-sidebar.png" alt="Connections sidebar" />
</Frame>

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/connections/add-connection.png" alt="Add connection" />
</Frame>

### Step 2: Select SFTP File Server

Under the **File Server** category, select **SFTP File Server**. Click **Details** to learn more, or click **+ Add Connection** to proceed.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/connections/add-sftp-connection.png" alt="Add SFTP connection" />
</Frame>

### Step 3: Accept Pipedream Integration

Graphium AI uses Pipedream to connect your SFTP server account. When the Pipedream Integration popup appears, simply click **Continue**.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/connections/confirm-pipedream.png" alt="Confirm Pipedream integration" />
</Frame>

### Step 4: Configure SFTP Authentication

Enter your server credentials in the Pipedream authentication form:

- **Hostname** — The network address of the SFTP server, either a domain name (e.g., `sftp.examplehospital.com`) or an IP address (e.g., `198.51.100.42`). Your server administrator can provide this.
- **Username** — The account name the SFTP server recognizes for Graphium AI to log in as. Your server administrator can provide this.
- **Private Key** — The full contents of an SSH private key, including the `-----BEGIN…-----` and `-----END…-----` lines. This is used for key-based authentication. The corresponding public key must already be installed on the SFTP server's `~/.ssh/authorized_keys` file for the username above. If you don't have a key pair yet, your server administrator can generate one and share the private key with you.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/connections/configure-pipedream-sftp.png" alt="Configure Pipedream SFTP authentication" />
</Frame>

### Step 5: Save the Connection

If successful, you should see a **Successful Connection** notification appear from Pipedream. Simply click **Continue**.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/connections/sftp-pipedream-successful.png" alt="SFTP Pipedream successful connection" />
</Frame>

Next, click the **Test** button in the top right corner to sync your data from your FTP/SFTP server. You will want to ensure the FTP/SFTP Server connection shows **"Healthy"** otherwise your data will not sync or migrate over to Graphium AI.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/connections/sftp-healthy.png" alt="SFTP connection healthy status" />
</Frame>

### Step 6: Set Sync Settings

Configure how often Graphium should check the server for new or updated files:

- **Auto-sync** — toggle on to enable automatic monitoring
- **Interval** — set the check frequency (e.g., every 5 minutes)

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/connections/auto-sync-settings.png" alt="Auto-sync settings" />
</Frame>

## What to Expect

Once connected, the status badge shows **"healthy"** and data begins syncing based on your configured interval. Workflows can now use this connection to trigger on new files detected on the server or to push files from Graphium to the server. All file transfer activity appears in the connection's Activity Log.

**Next steps:**

- Map vault tables to your FTP/SFTP data source so incoming files can flow into Graphium AI.
- Set up workflows or autonomous actions that react to new or updated files.
- Ask your AI Assistant questions about the synced file data once tables are populated.

## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Likely Cause | Solution |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| Pipedream Integration popup does not appear | Browser is blocking popups for Graphium AI | Allow popups for the Graphium AI domain and retry Step 3 |
| **"Successful Connection"** notification does not appear after entering credentials | Invalid credentials or the server is unreachable from the public internet | Confirm the hostname resolves, the server is online, and the username and private key are correct |
| Pipedream rejects the Private Key | Key is passphrase-protected, in the wrong format, or the matching public key is not authorized on the server | Generate a passphrase-less key in OpenSSH or PEM format and ask your server administrator to add the matching public key to `~/.ssh/authorized_keys` |
| Status shows "error" after setup | Incorrect host, username, or private key | Double-check server details in the Authentication section |
| Connection times out during Test | Firewall or network restriction | Confirm the server allows inbound connections from Graphium's IP range |
| Connection status does not show **"Healthy"** after clicking Test | Authentication succeeded but the server rejected the session, or the configured directory is inaccessible | Verify the username has read/write access to the target directory and re-run Test |
| **SFTP File Server** option is missing from the **File Server** category | Connection type may not be enabled for your workspace | Contact [support@graphium.ai](mailto:support@graphium.ai) to confirm availability |
| **+ Add Connection** button is not available in the vault sidebar | Insufficient vault role | Ask a vault Admin to grant Admin or Builder access |
| Auto-sync toggle cannot be enabled | Connection is in an unhealthy state | Resolve any authentication errors with Test first, then enable Auto-sync |
| Files are not being detected | Incorrect directory path configured | Review the server-specific settings in the connection detail view |
| Sync completes but no records appear in vault tables | Tables are not yet mapped to the FTP/SFTP data source | Open the table settings and configure the file source mapping |
| Status flips between Healthy and Error intermittently | Server session timeouts, IP rotation, or rate limiting | Check the server's auth log for repeated failed logins and consider allowlisting Graphium's IP range |

